text: Park County is a county found in the U.S. state of Montana. As of the 2020 census, there were 17,191 people. Its county seat is Livingston. A small part of Yellowstone National Park is in the extreme southern part of the county. It was created in February 23, 1887. == References == Category:1880s establishments in Montana Territory Category:1887 establishments in the United States Category:Montana counties
title: Park County, Montana
